physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Superficial, filamentous, submucosal mass (diameter, 0.2 mm) in a sinusoidal shape, total size ∼1.0 cm² in the mouth.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Over 4 days, the mass migrated from the right side of the buccal mucosa to the midline of the lower lip and then deeper under the vermilion border of the lip, becoming barely visible before migrating back to a more superficial position.

physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Normal complete blood count with no increase in eosinophils.
Migration of a nematode-like structure noted, visible as a serpiginous, transparent form.
